01855 /**
01856  * cvmx_ilk_rid_cfg
01857  */
01858 union cvmx_ilk_rid_cfg {
01859     uint64_t u64;
01860     struct cvmx_ilk_rid_cfg_s {
01861 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
01862     uint64_t reserved_39_63               : 25;
01863     uint64_t max_cnt                      : 7;  /**< Maximum number of reassembly IDs (RIDs) allowed for both links. If
01864                                                          an SOP arrives and the total number of RIDs already allocated to
01865                                                          both links is at least [MAX_CNT], the packet is dropped.
01866                                                          An SOP allocates a RID; an EOP frees a RID. ILK_RX()_RID can be used to further
01867                                                          restrict each link individually. */
01868     uint64_t reserved_7_31                : 25;
01869     uint64_t base                         : 7;  /**< The base RID for ILK. There is a shared pool of 96 RIDs for all MACs.
01870                                                          See PKI_REASM_E. ILK can allocate any RID in the range of
01871                                                          _ [BASE] -> ([BASE]+([MAX_CNT]-1)).
01872                                                          BASE and MAX_CNT must be constrained such that:
01873                                                          _ 1) [BASE] >= 2.
01874                                                          _ 2) [BASE] + [MAX_CNT] <= 96.
01875                                                          _ 3) [BASE]..([BASE]+([MAX_CNT]-1)) does not overlap with any other MAC programming.
01876                                                          The reset value for this CSR has been chosen such that all these conditions are satisfied.
01877                                                          The reset value supports up to a total of 64 outstanding incomplete packets between ILK0
01878                                                          and ILK1.
01879                                                          Changes to BASE must only occur when ILK0 and ILK1 are both quiescent (i.e. Both ILK0 and
01880                                                          ILK1 receive interfaces are down and the RX fifo is empty). */
01881 #else
01882     uint64_t base                         : 7;
01883     uint64_t reserved_7_31                : 25;
01884     uint64_t max_cnt                      : 7;
01885     uint64_t reserved_39_63               : 25;
01886 #endif
01887     } s;
01888     struct cvmx_ilk_rid_cfg_s             cn78xx;

02136                                                          correct operation of the link. */

02139                                                          1 to 288. */

02142                                                          same lane should not be enabled in multiple ILK_RXx_CFG0.  Each
02143                                                          bit of LANE_ENA maps to a RX lane (RLE) and a QLM lane.  NOTE:
02144                                                          LANE_REV has no effect on this mapping.
02145 
02146                                                                LANE_ENA[0] = RLE0 = QLM1 lane 0
02147                                                                LANE_ENA[1] = RLE1 = QLM1 lane 1
02148                                                                LANE_ENA[2] = RLE2 = QLM1 lane 2
02149                                                                LANE_ENA[3] = RLE3 = QLM1 lane 3
02150                                                                LANE_ENA[4] = RLE4 = QLM2 lane 0
02151                                                                LANE_ENA[5] = RLE5 = QLM2 lane 1
02152                                                                LANE_ENA[6] = RLE6 = QLM2 lane 2
02153                                                                LANE_ENA[7] = RLE7 = QLM2 lane 3 */
02154 #else

02681 /**
02682  * cvmx_ilk_rx#_mem_cal0
02683  *
02684  * Notes:
02685  * Software must program the calendar table prior to enabling the
02686  * link.
02687  *
02688  * Software must always write ILK_RXx_MEM_CAL0 then ILK_RXx_MEM_CAL1.
02689  * Software must never write them in reverse order or write one without
02690  * writing the other.
02691  *
02692  * A given calendar table entry has no effect on PKO pipe
02693  * backpressure when either:
02694  *  - ENTRY_CTLx=Link (1), or
02695  *  - ENTRY_CTLx=XON (3) and PORT_PIPEx is outside the range of ILK_TXx_PIPE[BASE/NUMP].
02696  *
02697  * Within the 8 calendar table entries of one IDX value, if more
02698  * than one affects the same PKO pipe, XOFF always wins over XON,
02699  * regardless of the calendar table order.
02700  *
02701  * Software must always read ILK_RXx_MEM_CAL0 then ILK_RXx_MEM_CAL1.  Software
02702  * must never read them in reverse order or read one without reading the
02703  * other.
02704  */

02708 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD

02710     uint64_t entry_ctl3                   : 2;  /**< XON/XOFF destination for entry (IDX*8)+3
02711

02713                                                                             remote tranmitter to the PKO pipe selected
02714                                                                             by PORT_PIPE3.
02715 
02716                                                          - 1: Link           Apply the backpressure received from the
02717                                                                             remote transmitter to link backpressure.
02718                                                                             PORT_PIPE3 is unused.
02719 
02720                                                          - 2: XOFF           Apply XOFF to the PKO pipe selected by
02721                                                                             PORT_PIPE3.
02722 
02723                                                          - 3: XON            Apply XON to the PKO pipe selected by
02724                                                                             PORT_PIPE3. The calendar table entry is
02725                                                                             effectively unused if PORT_PIPE3 is out of
02726                                                                             range of ILK_TXx_PIPE[BASE/NUMP].
02727 
02728                                                          This field applies to one of bits <52>, <44>, or <28> in the
02729                                                          Interlaken control word. */
02730     uint64_t port_pipe3                   : 7;  /**< Select PKO port-pipe for calendar table entry (IDX*8)+3

02732                                                          PORT_PIPE3 must reside in the range of ILK_TXx_PIPE[BASE/NUMP]
02733                                                          when ENTRY_CTL3 is "XOFF" (2) or "PKO port-pipe" (0). */

03437                                                          current value. */

03531                                                          ILK_INTSN_E::ILK_RXLNE()_SCRM_SYNC_LOSS. */

03536                                                          regain word boundary sync. Throws ILK_INTSN_E::ILK_RXLNE()_BDRY_SYNC_LOSS. */
03537     uint64_t serdes_lock_loss             : 1;  /**< RX SerDes loses lock. Throws ILK_INTSN_E::ILK_RXLNE()_SERDES_LOCK_LOSS. */
03538 #else

04174                                                          _ [LANE_ENA<13>] = TLE13  =  QLM7 lane 1.
04175                                                          _ [LANE_ENA<14>] = TLE14  =  QLM7 lane 2.
04176                                                          _ [LANE_ENA<15>] = TLE15  =  QLM7 lane 3. */

04197     struct cvmx_ilk_txx_cfg0_cn68xx {

04201                                                          transmit & receive clocks, skip word are  inserted/deleted */

04205                                                          software to send a packet containing a programmable pattern.
04206                                                          While in this mode, the scramblers and disparity inversion will
04207                                                          be disabled.  In addition, no framing layer control words will
04208                                                          be transmitted (ie. no SYNC, scrambler state, skip, or
04209                                                          diagnostic words will be transmitted).

04212                                                          enabling/disabling this mode. */

04216                                                          flow control status.  Otherwise, the multi-use field will

04219                                                               First control word:
04220                                                                Entry 0  = link
04221                                                                Entry 1  = backpressue id 0
04222                                                                Entry 2  = backpressue id 1
04223                                                                ...etc.
04224                                                             Second control word:
04225                                                                Entry 16 = link
04226                                                                Entry 17 = backpressue id 15
04227                                                                Entry 18 = backpressue id 16
04228                                                                ...etc.
04229                                                          This continues until the status for all 64 backpressue ids gets
04230                                                          transmitted (ie. 0-68 calendar table entries).  The remaining 3
04231                                                          calendar table entries (ie. 69-71) will always transmit XOFF.
04232 
04233                                                          To disable backpressure completely, enable the calendar table
04234                                                          and program each calendar table entry to transmit XON */
04235     uint64_t mfrm_len                     : 13; /**< The quantity of data sent on each lane including one sync word,
04236                                                          scrambler state, diag word, zero or more skip words, and the
04237                                                          data  payload.  Must be large than ILK_TXX_CFG1[SKIP_CNT]+9.
04238                                                          Supported range:ILK_TXX_CFG1[SKIP_CNT]+9 < MFRM_LEN <= 4096) */
04239     uint64_t brst_shrt                    : 7;  /**< Minimum interval between burst control words, as a multiple of
04240                                                          8 bytes.  Supported range from 8 bytes to 512 (ie. 0 <
04241                                                          BRST_SHRT <= 64) */
04242     uint64_t lane_rev                     : 1;  /**< Lane reversal.   When enabled, lane striping is performed from
04243                                                          most significant lane enabled to least significant lane
04244                                                          enabled.  LANE_ENA must be zero before changing LANE_REV. */
04245     uint64_t brst_max                     : 5;  /**< Maximum size of a data burst, as a multiple of 64 byte blocks.
04246                                                          Supported range is from 64 bytes to 1024 bytes. (ie. 0 <
04247                                                          BRST_MAX <= 16) */
04248     uint64_t reserved_25_25               : 1;
04249     uint64_t cal_depth                    : 9;  /**< Number of valid entries in the calendar.  CAL_DEPTH[2:0] must
04250                                                          be zero.  Supported range from 8 to 288.  If CAL_ENA is 0,
04251                                                          this field has no effect and the calendar depth is 72 entries. */
04252     uint64_t reserved_8_15                : 8;
04253     uint64_t lane_ena                     : 8;  /**< Lane enable mask.  Link is enabled if any lane is enabled.  The
04254                                                          same lane should not be enabled in multiple ILK_TXx_CFG0.  Each
04255                                                          bit of LANE_ENA maps to a TX lane (TLE) and a QLM lane.  NOTE:
04256                                                          LANE_REV has no effect on this mapping.
04257 
04258                                                                LANE_ENA[0] = TLE0 = QLM1 lane 0
04259                                                                LANE_ENA[1] = TLE1 = QLM1 lane 1
04260                                                                LANE_ENA[2] = TLE2 = QLM1 lane 2
04261                                                                LANE_ENA[3] = TLE3 = QLM1 lane 3
04262                                                                LANE_ENA[4] = TLE4 = QLM2 lane 0
04263                                                                LANE_ENA[5] = TLE5 = QLM2 lane 1
04264                                                                LANE_ENA[6] = TLE6 = QLM2 lane 2
04265                                                                LANE_ENA[7] = TLE7 = QLM2 lane 3 */
04266 #else
04267     uint64_t lane_ena                     : 8;
04268     uint64_t reserved_8_15                : 8;
04269     uint64_t cal_depth                    : 9;
04270     uint64_t reserved_25_25               : 1;
04271     uint64_t brst_max                     : 5;
04272     uint64_t lane_rev                     : 1;
04273     uint64_t brst_shrt                    : 7;
04274     uint64_t mfrm_len                     : 13;
04275     uint64_t cal_ena                      : 1;
04276     uint64_t mltuse_fc_ena                : 1;
04277     uint64_t lnk_stats_ena                : 1;
04278     uint64_t reserved_55_55               : 1;
04279     uint64_t ptrn_mode                    : 1;
04280     uint64_t reserved_57_60               : 4;
04281     uint64_t int_lpbk                     : 1;
04282     uint64_t ext_lpbk                     : 1;
04283     uint64_t ext_lpbk_fc                  : 1;
04284 #endif
04285     } cn68xx;
04286     struct cvmx_ilk_txx_cfg0_cn68xx       cn68xxp1;
04287     struct cvmx_ilk_txx_cfg0_s            cn78xx;
04288     struct cvmx_ilk_txx_cfg0_s            cn78xxp1;
04289 };
04290 typedef union cvmx_ilk_txx_cfg0 cvmx_ilk_txx_cfg0_t;
